    <item>
      <title>12.19 The Pursuer</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-19-the-pursuer/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-19-the-pursuer/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 08 Dec 2023 03:45:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;12.19 The Pursuer&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-18-rabbit-and-dragon/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8216;&lt;em&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t factor the weirdo tactician into your calculations.&lt;/em&gt;’&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although he has earned such a wise saying, there were times when people were at a loss at what to do with him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That they were able to manage something with the broken heirloom was a godsend.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Just as I was thinking about destroying it or something, for our future’s sake.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They were saved by the matriarch&amp;#8217;s remark. As a result of that, the orb had been switched and the dragon’s claws reduced to three digits.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As a show of apology, Rahan was going to introduce them to a skilled craftsman, but…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hahaha. So, about our future—”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, we shall return to the banquet hall,” the matriarch cut in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Just as well. So shall I,” the U clan head agreed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, we also have other clans to socialise with.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Shin clan matriarch and the former head of the U clan were distant. Not only that, their followers were also watching them from a distance.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao looked to her side.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Don’t we have any snacks?” Rakan asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Rakan-sama, please wait a bit longer,” Erfan chided the weirdo tactician.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan was depressed, his glasses fogged up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hey,” Maomao prodded Rahan with a whisper. “So what was the thing you said about negotiating to demand gratitude?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I know,” Rahan bit back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wondered what she could do. She decided to return to the banquet hall for the time being.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao returned to the banquet hall to find that a commotion had broken out at the Ra table. Out of curiosity, she moved closer to see Rahan’s older brother in an argument with an unknown man. Yao and En’en stood behind him. The opposing side consisted of the man in the argument and a somewhat familiar-looking man standing behind him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Who was he again?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was bad at remembering faces and names. The familiar man had a terrible posture. His movements looked stiff.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ahh!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao remembered who he was. If she wasn’t mistaken, he was the one who had been beaten up by Basen and got carried into the medical office.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Why was he in an argument with Rahan’s older brother?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I told you I have business with Yao-san. I don’t have business with you,” the unknown man said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan’s older brother countered, “Who the hell are you?! My name is–”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-san, come meet my family.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He pushed Rahan’s older brother aside, and attempted to hold Yao’s hand. The two bodyguards were glaring at him, so the pursuer couldn’t reach her, but he was armed with a sword.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This man…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan briskly returned to the table.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What are you doing?” Rahan came in to stop him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can’t you see?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan joining them only just added to the number of weak-looking men. The annoying pursuer didn’t bother to take Rahan on as an opponent.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The weirdo tactician hadn’t returned. Speaking of what he was doing, he had stopped in the path of a servant who was carrying food, and stole food from the tray. Erfan was with the weirdo tactician.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is no good, &lt;/em&gt;Maomao thought, when a helping hand emerged.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What are you doing?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The dignified voice belonged to the Shin clan’s matriarch.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Great aunt, it’s been a while.” The pursuer and the injured man got down on their knees in front of the matriarch.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Spare me the greetings. Not only are you tardy, you’ve gotten yourself into some kind of argument. Care to explain why?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tardy, huh.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They had let down their guard since this guy hadn’t been around in the beginning of the banquet.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There is a woman I wish to introduce to Grand Aunt. She is the one.” The annoying man, without a stain in his conscience, introduced Yao. “Her name is Yao. Although she isn’t from a named clan, her uncle is Vice Minister Lu. Her pedigree is satisfactory to be a bride for our family.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was terrifying how he said that with total confidence. The injured man also averted his eyes slightly. He was acting as support because they were family, but it seems he was aware of the annoying man’s lack of common sense.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Bride, you say. Does the young lady over there consent to this?” the matriarch asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“These are just his words. I have no intention of getting married yet,” Yao said resolutely. The way she could speak her mind when a normal young lady would be cowering, was her strong &lt;em&gt;and &lt;/em&gt;weak point.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The person’s opinion doesn’t matter. Our lineage is a good match, so you should just talk to the parents. Isn’t that what a woman is?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yao’s face stiffened. En’en looked like she was ready to take out a concealed weapon from her lapels.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, the women of Li are typically married in the way the annoying man said. Commoners may have it differently, but a young lady from a good family like Yao had no say in the matter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That being said, the annoying man wasn’t being logical.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Isn’t he aiming for the moment her parents aren’t around?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No matter how you look at it, it’s cowardly of you to go seek a discussion the moment her uncle, who is her guardian, is away.” Rahan’s older brother said what Maomao wanted to say.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There &lt;em&gt;is &lt;/em&gt;her mother, no?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Mother? Doubtful you could pay respect to her mother when you don’t see the point in asking women for their opinion.” Rahan’s older brother said bluntly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Outsiders should stay out of this.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They were going around in circles.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s like talking to a wall.” The matriarch looked exasperated. “If you wish to introduce her to me, I’d rather you do it in the right order.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But Yao-san’s father has long passed away. Considering her mother and her circumstances, what is so unsatisfying about her becoming my wife?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was nauseating how he could say contradictory things so brazenly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even Rahan, who had an expression like he honestly didn’t want to involve himself in this, was looking at him in contempt. He laughed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s so funny?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nothing. Spoken like a true unpopular guy, I just thought,” Rahan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You dare!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t only the pursuer; Rahan’s older brother’s eyes were also bloodshot for some reason.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The bodyguards immediately moved to stand beside Rahan, but he smoothly stopped them. “You keep harping on about lineage. The Shin clan does have a long history among the named clans, certainly. The Ra family with its shorter history is of no match. However…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan looked down on the man who was taller than him. It wasn’t a good look, but they were on opposing sides, so Maomao didn’t mind it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I am yet an underling who often runs errands for various departments. Lineage goes without saying, but if you wish to marry the niece of Vice Minister Lu with such self-confidence, you’ll certainly need to make a name for yourself. With all due respect, my opinion is inadequate, but may I have your name?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wow, right in the jugular.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan had keen eyes. He would remember people who could do their work even if they were from other departments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That guy was saying he’s from a named clan, but it doesn’t seem like he’s received the name. Well, not like I’m one to say,” Rahan’s older brother said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wh-what was that?!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As if Rahan’s older brother’s words had touched his sore spot, the man’s face turned bright red.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;More than being unpopular with woman, he’s more hurt over the fact that he didn’t receive a name even though he’s from a named clan, huh.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The target had completely shifted to Rahan’s older brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Y-you fucker! You dare mock me?!” The pursuer clenched his fist and was ready to swing it at Rahan’s older brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The bodyguards moved to stand in front of him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Stop it!” The matriarch’s voice resounded.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But this guy insulted me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And isn’t that the truth?!” The matriarch fired back mercilessly. It was when the man who accompanied her tried to stop her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s the commotion about?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao heard a familiar voice. She turned around. The Ma siblings, Basen and Mamei, were there. Basen, noticing the man he injured the other day, made a look of blatant distaste.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As for Mamei, her raptor eyes gleamed in a way similar to her mother’s.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s heaped.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao stealthily picked at the food at the table. Smart Rahan also sat down and joined her in eating. A hopeless man, he was.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;It looks like you have an argument over something,” Mamei called out to them like a friendly third party.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The pursuer who got reproached by the matriarch seemed to have decided to depend on the new spectators. “This man insulted me. As people from Ma, also of a military clan, you know what to do in a situation like this, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems he was acquainted with Basen. Being military officers, perhaps.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’d be a duel,” Basen replied extremely seriously.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A, a duel?!” Yao was flustered. “Isn’t a duel barbaric?” She glanced at Rahan’s older brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you ask for a witness, it’s legal. There’s also a training hall.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Basen was a muscle brain at a time like this. The other day he also used a practice match as an excuse to seriously injure a colleague.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems like Rahan’s older brother was dragged into something strange as usual, but both Rahan and Basen were calm. Maomao decided to remain as a bystander for the time being.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You insulted me, but who are you?! You’re sitting at the Ra table like you belong, but your face is new to me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;He wouldn’t have seen him before. Rahan’s older brother grew potatoes in a village. He didn’t serve in the imperial court.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This person isn’t related. He’s just a farmer!” Yao came forward to defend Rahan’s older brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That’ll have the opposite effect, the opposite effect.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao ate a grilled skewer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A farmer? A peasant, you say?” The pursuer smirked. “A peasant, huh. Why is a peasant sitting here? Turns out, the Ra clan is a gathering of eccentrics after all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Excuse me&lt;/em&gt;. The potatoes he grows are delicious,” Maomao said in spite of herself. She had whispered it; the opponent who was completely looking down on Rahan’s older brother didn’t notice.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The matriarch, exasperated, as it didn’t seem like her voice was getting to him either, came to stand in front of the pursuer. “Stay within your bounds! It is due to your own shortcomings that you were not given a name. Until you understand that, don’t even think about becoming my successor!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The pursuer looked vexed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Just as Maomao thought it would finally be resolved here, Rahan’s older brother came forward.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wait a moment. You insulted me too. If you meekly withdraw now, what does that make of &lt;em&gt;my &lt;/em&gt;standing?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Brother.” Rahan looked at his brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why don’t we settle this now? If you win against me, the Ra family will have no say about your marriage. But if you lose, give up on Yao-san completely.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sure thing.” The pursuer smirked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao surveyed her surroundings as she ate a skewer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yao was anxious. En’en couldn’t stop watching Yao in spite of the tension on her face.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The matriarch, fed up because of the pursuer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan was composed, Basen acted like it was somebody else’s problem, and Mamei was verifying the situation like Maomao was.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The pursuer, after hearing he was a farmer, was looking down on him. The injured man’s face was ashen.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The surprising thing was that Rahan’s older brother was rolling his shoulders, eager for the duel.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I wonder how it’d turn out.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Note that the weirdo tactician was snoring in the corner of the banquet hall.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: Fun fact, the pursuer and the injured guy are one and the same in the LN, and you do get his name (憂炎, Yuu&amp;#8217;en). &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;The word for pursuer can also mean someone or something that hangs around/follows someone closely. Something like a stalker, ig. Either way, it means a persistent son of a bitch. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-20-the-gong-crash-in-the-heart/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-19-the-pursuer/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4283-67bf5c0236721' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250226#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4283&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4283-67bf5c0236721' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4283-67bf5c0236721' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-19-the-pursuer/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
