    <item>
      <title>14.22 The End of Quarantine Life</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-22-the-end-of-quarantine-life/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-22-the-end-of-quarantine-life/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Feb 2025 11:02:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.22 The End of Quarantine&amp;nbsp;Life&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-21-attenuation/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They were finally released, ten days after their life in quarantine began.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ujun continued to feign ignorance until the end, and Yo continued to take care of the patient during that time. Maomao said nothing about this being a setup to Yo. Telling her would have been unfair and above all, she had no idea how that emotional girl would react.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Despite the uneasiness about who was behind it and why they did it plaguing her throughout, the opportunity for her to get answers finally presented itself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The characteristic sound of footfalls approached her, as if it were timed to the moment Yo left to inform their superiors of the patient’s record.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I am here to pick you uuuuup.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao only knew of one person who would drag out the end of her sentences like this.  “Chue-san, can you tell me what is going on?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had no idea when the military officer patient and Ujun left. She was the only one left in the clinic.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can’t be heeeelped.” Chue let herself into the clinic and started to prepare tea with great familiarity. As far as Maomao knew, Chue had never been here before, but since it was Chue, she accepted it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wiped down the table and received the tea from Chue. They had no snacks, so Chue took out steamed buns from her bosom pocket.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Tadah! They’ve been waaarmed.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“…” The warmth was subtle. Maomao purposely set it down beside the tea for it to cool. There might be a reason behind Chue acting somewhat theatrically, but since Maomao didn’t understand it, she ignored it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There were various complicated causes, and it was unavoidable. As for Jun-san, he asked to help to support his half-sister.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Uh huh.” Maomao had no idea how much of what Chue said was true, but she let it go for now. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“First off, what do you know about smallpox?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If her conjecture were true, then something similar to the appendicitis dosage experiment was being done with smallpox as well. “It looks more and more to me like some experimentation took place that I am not aware of.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was probably lent the banned book to have her understand what was going on. It was ultimately a copied version, not even a full copy to boot. “The words ‘smallpox vaccination’ appeared in the banned book. I was only handed a copy of that section, so it was easy to understand.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Being a banned book, there was no autopsy section. They probably thought it would be bad to take that section outside. With it missing, they could be excused even if anyone were to see it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The letter from Kokuyou had mentioned cows and horses. So it looks like the court physicians already made a move in that experiment, right?” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, they used the cows and horses from Red Plum Mansion where my brother-in-law’s sweetheart is staying. And Maomao-san, you have long realised this, right? The patient here was indeed one of the people who trialled that smallpox vaccinatiooon,” Chue replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was as Maomao imagined. “Was that person used to have me quarantined?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue let out an infuriating guffaw. “Haha, this time you’re the bonus, Maomao-saaan.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hm, then you mean, it wasn’t me…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8230;but Yo who was the main person to be quarantined?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What is the meaning of this?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue must have laughed to let Maomao know that she had been too self-conscious. If anything, Chue liked to provoke people, so Maomao decided to reply nonchalantly. She knew that getting angry would only have the opposite effect. “So this was to prevent Yo from going anywhere?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue winked and snapped her left fingers with a smile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Chue has a natural talent for provoking people&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why Yo? If it’s her relation to Kokuyou…” Maomao suddenly paused. People who were privy to Kokuyou’s smallpox vaccination method. She thought about the surviving villagers. And then, Yo’s family and that one other person. “&amp;#8230;Did someone in Yo-san’s family perform smallpox vaccinations of their own accord?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It makes things so easy, when there’s no need to explain to Maomao-saaan,” Chue said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao broke out entirely in sweat. Sweat from tension was different than sweat from exercise. Chue would probably have noticed by the smell.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It was thought that Yo-san was complicit, but seeing how she has been these past ten days, she seems to be unrelaaated.” As if to reassure Maomao, Chue first emphasised that Yo was innocent. “And regarding the smallpox vaccination, you’d understand if I just tell you that Yo-san’s family attempted it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Attempted?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It seems like Chue was trying to get Maomao to work it out. Maomao found it roundabout, but since she often replied like this, she couldn’t talk back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Yo is unrelated.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Yo’s family attempted the smallpox vaccination.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;They would need tissue from smallpox patients to do the vaccination.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo’s village had been devastated by smallpox years ago. Even if tissue from patients have been saved back then, they wouldn&amp;#8217;t be viable for vaccinations now.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Then, it would mean that they needed parts from relatively fresh smallpox patient.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Was Yo-san’s family encouraged by someone to do the vaccination and received parts from smallpox patients?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue made a circle with her fingers. “Correeect. It seems that certain someone would come during the day when Yo-san isn’t around. Yo-san’s mother is away, so only the children are at home. It seems like it has been kept a secret from Yo-san who returned from the front lines of the smallpox site.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And who is this person?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, it is the person Maomao is thinking of. It is the village head from Yo-san’s village. While the adults are away, the children are the only ones left at home. He must have heard from somewhere that the survivors of the village are residing in the capital. Being the former village head, the children must have let their guard down. That seems to be why they tried to copy the smallpox vaccination. Their mother noticed the abnormality, put a stop to it, and an incident broke out,” Chue said as she ate a steamed bun. Was the fact that she could eat while speaking without making a mess, a mark of a bride of a good family, even as degenerate as she was?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is better to not let Yo-san know about this. More importantly, does it mean that this large-scale staged act was started, based on the fact that the village head had yet to be arrested?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue nodded. “It seems the man of Yo-san’s family is helping out in the smallpox outbreak region. It would have been troubling if Yo-san were to know of it and it became a huge incident. In order to capture the village head when he returned, officers had been secretly stationed around her family home. The reason for this staged act was that so she could be quarantined in a way that wouldn’t arouse her suspicions.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Their attempt may have failed, but the fact that they were going to perform the smallpox vaccination of their own accord is a problem.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Children they may be, but they should expect a certain level of punishment. There was a possibility that Yo would run in a strange direction.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo was quite good for her age as a health worker, but she was too emotional.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although not as catastrophic as Tianyu, there was a part that was difficult to manage.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That’s right—it’s troubling, riiight? Yo-san still doesn’t know. And so, there was no way Yo-san could go home and if possible, we had to cut off all information as well. All so that she doesn’t find out there is surveillance around her home to try catch the village head.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao understood what Chue was getting at, but she had her doubts too. “Then why did you involve me too?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Haha, Yo-san would be reassured to have another woman with her, and—”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There is one more thing. In a time like this, we would want to have Rakan-sama&amp;#8217;s assistance.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao made an expression of disgust as always.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We even added the pretext that it was to protect Maomao-san from running into the village heaad.” Chue clapped her hands and brought out flags and flowers. Her silly act was quite strange.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Looks like the village head had visited various health care workers. Protecting Yo-san was also related to that.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was the pretext of ten day, but should she take it as the problem has already been resolved now that they have been released? “Then, the village head has been caught?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes… three days ago.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao didn’t overlook that evasive phrasing. “Was he not captured alive?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Not that.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The village head, the one called the random attacker, was found in the village that has been locked down due to smallpox. It seems the children spilled that Yo-san’s father is working theeere.” Chue clapped her hands. “And at the same time, Kokuyou-san was discovered stabbed by the random attacker.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“WHAT?!” Maomao jumped to her feet and smacked the table.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He’s alive. It was a little dangerous, but he made iiiit.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;The weirdo tactician was useless, huh?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The request for Rakan-sama’s assistance only extended to within the capital. He’s not someone who would pay attention to another town Maomao-san is not in, after all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A strange sense of guilt rose in Maomao. “So, what does Chue-san want me to do by explaining all this to me?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue had long finished her steamed bun so she was looking at Maomao’s. The bun was cold, but Maomao directly handed it over.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue took the steamed bun and fiddled with it as she spoke, “The village head has been captured. He’s not in a good condition. He’s acting like he’s been apprehended by something and is on his last legs. Everyone is neglecting him, saying that it’s a madman’s nonsense, but are you curious?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you telling me to give that person a check-up?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m not forcing youuu.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was unfair to say it like this.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao could only move in the direction her scale of troublesomeness and curiosity tipped towards.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-23-the-criminal/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-22-the-end-of-quarantine-life/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5323-67bf3f3e69744' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250226#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5323&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5323-67bf3f3e69744' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5323-67bf3f3e69744' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-22-the-end-of-quarantine-life/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
