    <item>
      <title>14.21 Attenuation</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-21-attenuation/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-21-attenuation/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 31 Jan 2025 11:46:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.21 Attenuation&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-20-a-new-casualty/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Not long after, Maomao and the others moved to another room. Should they continue to occupy the medical office, they would have gotten in the way of work.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When they were shown to the dosage experimentation site she had grown to know and love, she fell into an indescribable mood. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So there’s a place like this.” Ujun was surprised to see a clinic in town.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With the dosage experiments scaled down when the emperor’s surgery ended without incident, there were a lot of empty rooms.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The patient was carried over in a cage. Maomao and the others walked over with their mouths covered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I don’t think Maomao-san is infected,” Yo said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought so too, but she had that niggling feeling from touching the rashes when she undid the bandages. She washed her hands right after, so the chance of infection was low. Maomao decided to turn to the higher ups to make the judgement call.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Be sure to stay put for a while.&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If that was what Court Physician Liu told her, there was nothing else she could do.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are there enough workers?” Maomao wondered, but she could only abide by the words of her superior.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I’m also worried about Yo.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, Yo worked briskly and she was well-versed with the patient. She might struggle with a couple of patients, but with only one, she managed just fine on her own.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They would each be staying in a room by themselves at the clinic. As for their meals, they would pick them up from the dining hall. They would also be sharing the toilet, but other than that, they wouldn&amp;#8217;t be leaving their rooms.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo’s room was next to Maomao’s. The patient was quarantined in a room a short distance away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was lying sprawled out while reading the books she had accumulated. Thanks to Ujun requesting books, Maomao also requested for more.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The most important thing was the book that was currently in her hands.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I have Kada’s book!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was given one of the copies of the tattered book that had been restored. Normally, being a banned book, it was forbidden to be taken out, but she got special permission.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;They even copied Kokuyou’s research materials. She had enjoyed comparing the two texts so much she lost track of time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kada’s book was moth-eaten in places, so Maomao needed to supplement it with her own knowledge and Kokuyou’s materials. It was a fun activity that used her brain. Although, it was unfortunate that she couldn&amp;#8217;t gather her thoughts by taking notes, since banned books weren&amp;#8217;t allowed to be copied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;To avoid contracting smallpox, one must catch a weaker form of smallpox beforehand.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;There is still a chance of aggravation from the weaker form of the toxin.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had a lot of knowledge as well. She reviewed her knowledge as she read the book.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;There is also a chance of gaining resistance from contracting a very similar disease.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A very similar disease.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao heard the sound of footsteps. She could tell it was Yo who was returning to her room next door.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Maomao-san, how are you?&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo asked about her condition from the other side of the door.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I think I&amp;#8217;m fine, but I’m not allowed to leave, yeah?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;It goes without saying.&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao understood as well. “How is the patient?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;He has a rash, but it didn’t spread much. He also has a fever, but it&amp;#8217;s receding surprisingly quickly.&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She could tell that Yo was making a mystified expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What if it’s not smallpox?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;No, the symptoms resemble smallpox, and since he’s a military officer, it would mean that he is physically fit. He might have caught a weaker variant by chance&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao groaned, in agreement as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Leaving that aside, there’s something that’s been bothering me. Can I ask you&lt;/em&gt;?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is it?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Why did Maomao-san respond to that cut? I wouldn’t have been convinced that it was smallpox based on that&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Right&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo wasn’t yet informed about the random attacker case. There was a random attacker who was spreading the seeds of smallpox, and Kokuyou was under suspicion. Court Physician Liu probably didn’t speak to Yo about this to avoid getting her personal feelings involved in the matter about Kokuyou.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao opened her mouth while wondering what she should do. Yo would probably trust Kokuyou. Maomao also wanted to believe in him. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Actually…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She talked about the random attacker.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Doctor wouldn’t do such a thing&lt;/em&gt;!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As expected, Yo rejected the notion. Judging by her raised voice, Maomao could tell that the girl’s emotions were stirred up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Of course I know that. It&amp;#8217;s just that I can’t think of anyone else who would use this method to inoculate the seeds of smallpox. Supposing that there isn’t anyone else who saw that method personally. Yo-san mentioned it before, right? How there was another survivor from your village aside from your family and a couple of children.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Ah, that…&lt;/em&gt;” Yo hesitated. “&lt;em&gt;Yes. There is one person. The witch doctor, who was the village head at the time.&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The witch doctor.” If Maomao remembered correctly, it was the person who drove Kokuyou out. She didn’t think it would be that person, of all people.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;But I don’t think the village head would copy Doctor. He was so against what Doctor did, after all.”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo was bewildered, but Maomao felt like she understood their feelings on the contrary.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“In truth, he might have tried it out once he knew what Kokuyou did was correct.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;He should’ve just dropped dead.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao didn’t voice her thoughts. She only considered how he survived. “Was the village head wealthier than the other villagers?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“.&lt;em&gt;..Most probably. He did purchase food in bulk as our representative&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With good nutrition, the chance of survival increased. She also had another consideration in mind.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Could he have caught smallpox before?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;I… don’t know about that. Although, he said that it’s because he&amp;#8217;s a witch doctor, so he always wore clothes that covered his skin. Ah, but also—&lt;/em&gt;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;He said that he will never catch diseases, because those are a result of a curse&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao took it as that this village head wasn’t a witch doctor but a swindler.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The people at a village settlement would be either impoverished or those who could no longer return to their former places. The village head must be the latter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Suppose the village head is the random attacker, what do we do?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;I’ll never forgive him! I can’t believe he would not only chase out Doctor and also cause trouble to others!”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We can’t decide that the village head is the culprit, but just in case, it might be good if you can tell us what he looks like and we can draw up a portrait.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Yes&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“This is only just in case.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;I know&lt;/em&gt;.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao emphasised her words so that Yo didn’t charge ahead. The girl had an emotional side. It would be scary if Maomao didn’t underscore her point.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&lt;em&gt;Now&amp;#8217;s not the time. I will prioritise watching the patient’s condition&lt;/em&gt;,” Yo said, as if she had given up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The patient’s condition was mild. His fever broke in a few days and he asked when he could return to work.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Absolutely not!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo was audibly yelling, probably because the patient tried to leave the clinic.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Smallpox was the same as colds in how a person recently recovered was still contagious. More than anything, it was said that scabs were contagious for a year even. There was no way they could simply let him out in public.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sounds like she’s having a tough time,” Ujun said from a short distance away. It seemed he was here to pick up his meal just like Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Looks like Ujun-san didn’t get any particular symptoms either,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please call me Jun.” Ujun gave her a carefree smile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although this man was from the U clan, he was pretty much expelled from the clan. The reason he called himself Ujun the other day was probably so it would be easier to remind Maomao whom he thought had forgotten him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even though he asked her to call him casually, she ignored him. She had folded back when Rikuson told her to address him without honorifics, but she figured that Ujun would be the one folding if she continued to ignore him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought that just because they were speaking more casually to each other, it didn’t necessarily mean that they were a lot closer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Looks like it’s about time for us to go outside too,” Ujun said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;With the patient, the source of the infection, this energetic, it would seem like Maomao and the others would be fine as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I guess so.” Maomao looked at Ujun’s demeanour and thought, &lt;em&gt;I knew it&lt;/em&gt;. “More importantly, what is your intention with this charade?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Charade?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao picked up her meal from the table and rudely ate with her hands. “The military officer was injured by the random attacker while on duty, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, that’s what I’ve heard.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The cut was on his forearm, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I knew it&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao sighed. “I believe a military officer who is on patrol around town would be wearing arm guards. Wouldn’t that be a difficult place for a random attacker to slash at?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Ujun smiled ambiguously at her question.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;He reminds me of someone.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue came to mind.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had been deceived by Chue in the western capital. If not for that experience, she wouldn’t have hit upon this idea now. “Was it a trick to have me quarantined?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I don’t know what you are talking about.” Ujun pretended to know nothing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If this was just a mistake in Maomao’s speculation, that was fine. The man called Ujun would forget Maomao’s nonsense. However, it was a different matter if her speculation was correct.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao changed the topic. “Do you know where Lishu-sama, your younger sister, is right now, Ujun-san?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I hear she has retired to religion.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“She is at a place called Red Plum Mansion that gathers eccentric people. Lishu-sama is raising ducks there.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ducks?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“They also raise horses and cows.” Maomao recalled that Kokuyou was looking for horses and cows.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She also requested to be brought to that place. However, would the court physicians already know of Kokuyou’s project by now?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kada’s book, Kokuyou’s research materials, and horses and cows.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;To be resistant to smallpox, one must contract a weaker form of the disease.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;One may also acquire resistance from catching a related disease.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And humans may catch diseases from livestock as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“A disease that is like smallpox for horses and cows. People would contract the same disease if you inoculate them with it. Ujun-san, is it not the case that the patient you brought in had been inoculated with the seed of that disease?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She didn’t think Ujun came here by chance.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please call me Jun.” Ujun was all smiles.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you playing dumb?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m just saying what I’m saying. The one with U in his name is a suspicious insignificant person, so he cannot turn down what has been requested of him.” He confessed that he had done as he was told.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao let out a heavy sigh. Ujun may be an insignificant person, but it looked like he knew how to live as one.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“However, I am curious about how Lishu-sama is faring. I was just told that if I wanted to know, I should bring this patient to the medical office.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although Maomao didn’t know how much of what he was saying was true, it didn’t seem like he would give her details on what she wanted to know.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, I have a question. How many more days do I have to stay here?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Beats me. Everyone said that you need to be quarantined for around ten days. So, would that make it ten days?” Ujun answered while acting as though he knew nothing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-22-the-end-of-quarantine-life/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-21-attenuation/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5315-67bf3f3e82335' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20250226#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5315&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5315-67bf3f3e82335' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5315-67bf3f3e82335' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-21-attenuation/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
